-- Nordic Stocks: Aker Solutions, Cision, Munters, Vestas Wind Systems Move
-- Toby Alder
-- 2010-06-30T13:59:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/aker-solutions-ericsson-munters-nokia-may-move-nordic-stock-preview.html

          
          
             The  Stoxx Nordic 30 Index , the
benchmark measure for the region, rose 41.53, or 0.7 percent, to
6,324.92 at 3:56 p.m. in Stockholm, following yesterday’s 3.1
percent loss.  
 The  OMX Stockholm 30 Index  increased 1 percent while
Norway’s  OBX Index  rose 0.2 percent. The  Copenhagen 20 Index 
gained 0.8 percent, while the  Helsinki 25 Index  advanced 0.2
percent.  
 The following companies’ shares were among the most active
in Nordic markets today. Symbols are in parentheses.  
 Cision AB  (CSN SS) rose 2.7 percent to 5.70 kronor, erasing
yesterday’s 2.6 percent loss. The Swedish media-monitoring and
analysis company said it agreed to buy PIR Svenska AB to
strengthen its position in the Swedish market. PIR had full-year
sales of 8 million kronor ($1.03 million), Cision said in a
statement.  
 Munters AB  (MTRS SS) soared 10.5 percent to 47.50 kronor,
set to reach the highest level since May 20. The Swedish maker
of dehumidifiers said it agreed to sell its MCS division to
private equity company Triton. The deal will generate an
estimated net profit of 650 million kronor, it said.  
 Neste Oil Oyj  (NES1V FH) fell 2.4 percent to 12 euros,
extending yesterday’s 1.6 percent loss. Finland’s only oil
refiner was cut to "underweight" from "equal weight" at Morgan
Stanley.  
 Separately, Neste Oil sold its Sines plant in Portugal to
 Repsol Polimeros LDA , reducing its annual capacity by 50,000
tons, it said in a statement today.  
